snippet.textDisplay: I became very popular on tiktok without warning and it kinda freaked me out but at the same time I just kept doing my own thing instead of doing what everyone else was doing on tiktok. I’m addiemarieart on there with the art tips and weird art videos... I started my account last May and today I have 83,500+ followers 💖 I’m grateful for everyone that has followed and supported my art channel so far. With popularity comes more mean people out of nowhere that I normally wouldn’t see if I wasn’t popular (and I’m just an art channel on tiktok, can’t imagine the amount of hate that actual creators handle or avoid day to day on there). To everyone reading this: people go viral and gain popularity for numerous reasons, and the ones that last are the ones that have the talent and drive to carry themselves through it all both good and bad. You need to do your own thing and keep doing it to become something new and not just copy what everyone else does to truly stand out.
